Vice President Mike Pence gave a speech at the Indiana Statehouse in Indianapolis, thanking the people of Indiana for their support and for the opportunities he has been given to serve. He expressed his gratitude to his family, including his wife Karen and their children, and to the previous governors of Indiana. Pence also discussed the portrait that was unveiled during the event, explaining the significance of certain elements in the painting. He concluded his speech by expressing his commitment to continue serving the country as Vice President.